         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Private ¶ 21/1/95 ¶  ¶ During some of the next weeks, dear Mr Rodway, questions, which gravely affect my branch of the public service, ¶  will have to be solved, so that I have neither leisure nor tra...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">95.01.21</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Leonard Rodway</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">ML DOC.2492, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">Transcribed 6.1.92. To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>Private</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">21/1/95</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>During some of the next weeks, dear Mr Rodway, questions, which gravely affect my branch of the public service,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">What is this about?</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> will have to be solved, so that I have neither leisure nor tranquillity to work critically on plants of any kind. Wait therefore kindly a little longer for my giving opinions on your Carex and other recently sent plants. I have put all the Tasmanian plants, yet to be examined, together on my working table.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I wonder, you cannot muster Wolffia nor more Lemnas for Tasmania.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With regardful remembrance your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Will you use my simplified form of DC's system for your Flora of Tasm?<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">Does he?</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> Whatever you do, keep not up the chaotic Monochlamydeae.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I will send you in the course of this week typic specimens of the 3 plants, as desired by you. My Office is a long way from the Herbarium, so it can happen, that obtaining particular material out of it, about a <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">million</hi>
               </seg> sheets, takes some time.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
